{"parse":{"title":"A Desk for Billie","pageid":50898667,"revid":797620877,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox vevent\" style=\"width:22em;font-size:90%;\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" class=\"summary\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-size:110%;font-style:italic;\">A Desk for Billie</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:A_Desk_for_Billie_1956_title.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"A Desk for Billie 1956 title.png\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/0/0e/A_Desk_for_Billie_1956_title.png/220px-A_Desk_for_Billie_1956_title.png\" width=\"220\" height=\"163\" class=\"thumbborder\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/0/0e/A_Desk_for_Billie_1956_title.png/330px-A_Desk_for_Billie_1956_title.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/0/0e/A_Desk_for_Billie_1956_title.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"366\" data-file-height=\"272\" /></a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;padding-right:0.65em;\">Directed by</th><td>\nIrving Rusinow</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;padding-right:0.65em;\">Produced by</th><td>\nAgrafilms for <a href=\"/wiki/National_Education_Association\" title=\"National Education Association\">National Education Association</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;padding-right:0.65em;\">Music by</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/William_Bergsma\" title=\"William Bergsma\">William Bergsma</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-score_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-score-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;padding-right:0.65em;\"><div style=\"padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;white-space:normal;\">Release date</div></th><td>\n1956</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;padding-right:0.65em;\"><div style=\"padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;white-space:normal;\">Running time</div></th><td>\n57 minutes</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;padding-right:0.65em;\">Country</th><td>\nUnited States</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;padding-right:0.65em;\">Language</th><td>\nEnglish</td></tr></tbody></table> \n<p><i><b>A Desk for Billie</b></i> is an educational American film released by the <a href=\"/wiki/National_Education_Association\" title=\"National Education Association\">National Education Association</a> in 1956.<sup id=\"cite_ref-desk1_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-desk1-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>It is based on the story of Billie Davis, who grew up in a migrant family, and how she found educational opportunities.  Davis' story first came to public light when her story <i>I Was a Hobo Kid</i> appeared in the <i><a href=\"/wiki/Saturday_Evening_Post\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Saturday Evening Post\">Saturday Evening Post</a></i> in December 1952.<sup id=\"cite_ref-billiedavis_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-billiedavis-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-twotributes_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-twotributes-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>It was directed by Irving Rusinow, whose other fims included <i>Skippy and the Three R's</i> and <i>Freedom to Learn</i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-rusinow1_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-rusinow1-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-rusinowobit_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-rusinowobit-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>  The film won a Golden Reel Award in the Education category at the Fourth Annual American Film Assembly.<sup id=\"cite_ref-twotributes_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-twotributes-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-billboard_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-billboard-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Primary_cast\">Primary cast</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=A_Desk_for_Billie&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Primary cast\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>Billie as child - Nancy Pinet</li>\n<li>Billie as girl - Joan Lundy</li>\n<li>Father - A. Carroll Edwards</li>\n<li>Mother - Verna Brown</li>\n<li>1st teacher - Bernice Harvey</li>\n<li>2nd teacher - Melva Comfort</li>\n<li>3rd teacher - Peggy Greene</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=A_Desk_for_Billie&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist columns references-column-width\" style=\"-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em; list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-score-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-score_1-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">McCarty, Clifford <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=IK7tuydSUpQC&amp;pg=PA40&amp;lpg=PA40#v=onepage&amp;q&amp;f=false\">Film Composers in America: A Filmography, 1911-1970</a>, p. 40 (2000)</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-desk1-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-desk1_2-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=WJkEAAAAMAAJ&amp;q=%22a+desk+for+billy%22+movie&amp;dq=%22a+desk+for+billy%22+movie&amp;hl=en&amp;sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwituuLP07vNAhVJ0h4KHeTZCXkQ6AEILjAE\">Social Foundations of Educational Decisions</a>, p. 75 (1965)</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-billiedavis-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-billiedavis_3-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"